# Import the libraries
import keras.backend as K
import numpy as np

# Declare the data
A = np.random.rand(20,500)
B = np.random.rand(500,3000)

#Create Variable
x = K.variable(value=A)
y = K.variable(value=B)
z = K.dot(x,y)
print(K.eval(z))
